Job Description:
Telecom Specialist

 Are you looking for a company that works on major engineering projects all over the world? Do you want to make a difference by improving the daily lives of communities worldwide? Are you seeking to join an inclusive and diverse team that you can truly count on? You’ve come to the right place!

 Come join us in reshaping the future with AtkinsRéalis. AtkinsRéalis is dedicated in engineering a better future for our planet and its people.

 The Transmission, Distribution & Renewables division at AtkinsRéalis designs, develops, and delivers engineering, procurement, and construction solutions for high voltage power transmission line and substation projects in Alberta, British Columbia, Ontario and abroad. We have a great opportunity for a Telecom Specialist based out of our Burnaby, BC office. Our Telecom Specialists are primarily responsible for the delivery of telecommunication Specializing design with focus in the areas of microwave radio link design, high speed fiber optics link design as well as IP/MPLS based local and wide area networks for our high voltage transmission line and substation projects.

 Location: Burnaby, BC

 Your role within the team 
As a member of our Ports & Marine team, you will:

 Design of telecommunication facilities including Microwave and UHF radio links, fiber optic transmission links including the cable (ADSS and OPGW), SONET & SDH/TDM multiplex systems, IP/MPLS Network systems, tele protection, VSAT systems, cable protection systems, telecom power systems and telecom towers & antennas;
 Prepare project specifications for material/equipment purchase and installation and delivery of accurate and thorough designs that will meet industry standards and specifications as well as meet good engineering practices with excellent constructability;
 Resolve site queries, attending site meetings, and performing site inspections during the construction phase of projects;
 Maintain complete project documentation with respect to telecom design and construction, including all completion packages, as-built requirements and return data information;
 Coordinate design activities to maintain project schedules and ensure successful project completion and assist the Estimating Team in preparation of estimates and project proposals;
 Work within a multi-discipline team to design efficient and reliable telecommunication facilities, and review internal and external designs for code compliance with good design practice and constructability;
 Maintain good working relationships with internal groups that support projects such as procurement, project management, material suppliers, contractors, and any others that affect the quality, schedule, and cost of projects;
 Provide all design activities in accordance with all applicable codes and standards, including all AtkinsRéalis policies and procedures;
 Occasional travel to site locations is required.


 Why choose AtkinsRéalis as an employer?
 Because we offer:

 The opportunity to work on various major projects for internal and external clients;
 An exciting environment where work-life balance is important;
 A wide array of learning and development opportunities;
 Competitive pay, flexible benefits, an employee share plan, and a defined contribution pension plan;
 A work environment focused on health and safety.


 The ideal candidate

 Holds a bachelor’s degree in Telecom or Electrical Engineering, or equivalent;
 Is registered with EGBC or eligible for registration;
 At least 5 years of experience in Telecom Engineering, working on above mentioned technologies and demonstrated design experience;
 Knowledge of Canadian and British Columbia codes and standards, including OH&S Regulations, CSA codes is an asset;
 Experience in Utility Telecom Systems will be an asset;
 Co-op experience for junior candidates is an asset;
 Fluent in English with excellent written and oral communication.


 Are you up for this challenge? Apply today and join our team to help engineer a Better Future for our Planet and its People.

