 AtkinsRéalis’s Transmission, Distribution & Renewables Sector is a pioneer in the field of power generation and distribution. The team has been closely involved in the design, construction, refurbishment and study of hydro and power systems and has facilitated the production of some 296,000 MW of hydropower, more than 114,000 km of transmission lines and more than 2,500 substations around the world. We are currently looking for a Protection & Control Engineer-in-Training to join our team out of our Burnaby, BC office.

 Location: Burnaby, BC

 Your role within the team 
As a member of Transmission, Distribution and Renewables team, you will:


 Prepare Protection & Control designs from conceptual to implementation stage for Transmission, Distribution and Generating stations;
 Perform design work in accordance with the Canadian Electrical Code;
 Prepare single line diagrams, DC/AC control schematics;
 Design and development of panel layouts and bill of materials and detailed wiring diagrams;
 Develop cable block diagrams and cable and conduit schedules;
 Program Protection & Control devices;
 Work on reports and calculations and perform site visits;
 Work collaboratively with other team members to deliver projects.


