 Because we offer:


 The opportunity to work on various major projects for internal and external clients;
 An exciting environment where work-life balance is important;
 A wide array of learning and development opportunities;
 Competitive pay, flexible benefits, an employee share plan, and a defined contribution pension plan;
 A work environment focused on health and safety.


 The ideal candidate

 Holds a Bachelor’s Degree in Electrical Engineering or equivalent;
 Is registered as an EIT with EGBC or is eligible for registration;
 Has previous electrical design work experience in T&D and or Generation sector is an asset;
 Has taken courses in Protection & Control at a University level or equivalent;
 Must be willing to learn new technologies and programming of devices;
 Experience in a consulting environment is an asset;
 Experience with AutoCAD and PLC programming is an asset;
 Knowledge and application of the Canadian electrical code is an asset;
 Demonstrated excellent written and oral English communication skills and good work ethic.


