 Senior airside electrical engineer

 As part of AtkinsRéalis’ Engineering Services group, the Airports team specializes in providing a full range of planning and engineering services for airport and heliport infrastructure projects to local, national and international clients. Projects range from small assignments, such as runway extension studies and apron expansions, to airport master plans and taxiway and runway infrastructure rehabilitation projects.

 This position can be based anywhere in the province of Quebec or Ontario, with a preference for Quebec City, Montreal or Ottawa. The airport team currently operates on a hybrid work model, with our teams splitting their work week between home and office.

 Your role within the team
 To perform this role successfully, the candidate will be responsible for but not limited to the following:

 Acting as Lead Electrical Design and/or a Project Manager in the design, project management and contract administration for airfield infrastructure projects for private airports, regional and international airports;
 Oversee, lead and develop a scope for the engineering investigations and planning work that assist in preparation of design of the airfield infrastructure;
 Provide engineering services during construction activities by reviewing shop drawings for conformance with specifications; prepares records and progress reports defining construction progress;
 Assist and oversee the development and preparation of figures, design drawings, specifications, calculations, life cycle cost analysis, cost estimates, quantity take-offs, technical reports, design briefs etc.;
 Perform field inspections of construction when required;
 Mentor and support junior staff.


 Why choose AtkinsRéalis as an employer?
 Because we offer:

 The opportunity to work on various major projects for internal and external clients.
 An exciting environment where work-life balance is important.
 A wide array of learning and development opportunities.
 Competitive pay, flexible benefits, an employee share plan, and a defined contribution pension plan.
 A work environment focused on health and safety.


 The ideal candidate

 Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Electrical Engineering;
 OIQ Member (or eligible for licensing) with a minimum of 10 years related work experience;
 Working knowledge of computer programs and web-based applications such as MS Office suite, AutoCAD , Civil3D, AviPlan Aircraft Modelling software, FAARFEILD, PAVER software;
 Have knowledge and experience using FAA, ICAO and Transport Canada standards;
 Effective team player with excellent interpersonal skills with team members and clients;
 Ability to travel to project sites (some remote) for design purposes and resident construction services;
 Fluency in French and English, with excellent oral and written communication skills.


