 Project Controller

 If you are looking for an employer with large-scale international engineering projects to offer. If you want to make a difference to a multitude of communities by improving their daily lives. If you want to join an inclusive and diverse team you can count on…then we are the place for you!

 AtkinsRéalis is a Canadian world-leading engineering and construction group. We help owners bring their products to the market, offering services in engineering, procurement, construction, testing and commissioning, operation and maintenance, project management and project financing services to a wide variety of market sectors. Our employees are proud to build what matters.

 Your role within the team
 As a member of the Major Project team, you will report to the Project Control Manager and be responsible for:


 Support the construction team, monitoring progress, challenging and assisting them to deliver the project to the baseline and working on mitigations as required;
 Provide budgets and contribute to forecasting in close collaboration with the construction team ;
 Work closely with lead cost controller to produce monthly cost forecasts, weekly progress and cost reports and also change management;
 Work with subcontractors to ensure monthly invoices are captures or accrued, schedule of payments conform to project coding structure, changes are managed, etc;
 Collaborate closely with the procurement, cost, estimating, change, risk and other teams to execute the project;
 Produce weekly progress, S-curve, Earned Value and KPI reports, and the monthly report, and recommend corrective actions under the supervision of project controls manager .


 (The project controller we are looking for must have experience in building and industrial construction to support mandates in the Becancour aera. You will have the opportunity to join our Montreal or Quebec City Office and may have to travl to the site if necessary)

 Why choose AtkinsRéalis as an employer?
 Because we offer:

 The opportunity to work on diverse and large-scale projects, both domestically and internationally.
 A stimulating work environment where work-life balance is valued.
 Access to a wide range of training opportunities focused on individual development and interests.
 Competitive salary, flexible benefits, share ownership plan, and defined contribution pension plan.
 A work environment that prioritizes health and safety.


 Qualifications for the Project Controller

 Bachelor’s degree in civil engineering/construction engineering or College Diploma in civil engineering with relevant experience;
 5-10 years of experience in planning for all phases of project life cycle, ideally from design to execution;
 Knowledge of cost management tools, ERP’s, P6 and other project controls tools, software and systems ( JD Edwards, Aconex, etc.);
 Proficiency in use of MS Office suite, particularly Excel, and knowledge of dashboard tools (Power BI, etc.);
 Familiarity with AACEI Recommended Practices and other related documents;
 Excellent communication and writing skills, fluency in English and French.


