 AtkinsRéalis’s Infrastructure and Water Utilities team is in search of a Senior Hydrotechnical Engineer to join our growing team in Burnaby, BC or Calgary AB, reporting to the Director, Water Infrastructure Western Canada. Be part of a team that has been designing and building water infrastructure around the world for more than a century. We protect water sources, design water plants, return wastewater safely to the ecosystem, and finalize flood defence strategies. So, you’ll work with environmentally responsible teams who are always pushing research and innovation.

 Location: Burnaby, Vancouver, BC, or Calgary, AB

 Your role within the team 
As a member of our Infrastructure and Water Utilities team, you will:

 Lead hydrologic and hydraulic engineer and engineer of record with responsibility for design recommendations and deliverables;
 Perform hydrological/hydraulic analyses and design of transportation and hydropower projects related hydraulic structures including bridges, bridge size culverts, channels, intakes, conveyance systems, surge systems, spillways, and energy dissipation systems;
 Prepare hydrological/hydraulic studies including stormwater management, flood protection, dam safety reviews and assessments, preliminary and detailed design drawings, construction contract documents and special provisions; cost estimates and tender documents for above works;
 Business development and proposal preparation for civil and municipal work via RFPs process and project management to ensure quality of project deliverables on time and within budget.
 Lead, guide, and mentor a team of intermediate and junior staff.


