 The ideal candidate

 Holds a bachelor’s degree in Civil Engineering (Environmental or Water resources) or equivalent;
 Is registered as a Professional Engineer (P.Eng.) with EGBC or APEGA;
 Has at least 15 years of relevant experience and experience in preparing preliminary and detailed engineering design; contract specifications and special provisions; and tender documents;
 Has experience in the Canadian Highway Bridge Design Code and the BC Supplement to TAC Geometric Design Guide and experience in BC MOTI, AT, SK MOH and MTO transportation projects;
 Hands-on experience with AutoCAD, Civil 3D, GIS, Storm and water hydraulic modeling using software such as PCSWMM, HEC-RAS, HEC-HAMS, SWMHYMO, HY-8, FLO-3D, etc.;
 Strong technical report writing and communication skills, and ability to represent the design team to the client;
 Familiarity with municipal and provincial design standards in British Columbia and Alberta and other Canadian provinces;
 River Engineering experience is an asset.
 A valid driver’s license is required.


